   <talk_paragraph index="n1816_vernicka-accepting" image="" itemindex="" portrait_left="" portrait_right="Npc_Left_vernicka.dds" center_image="">
      <talk_answer link_index="n1816_vernicka-accepting-acceptted" mid="70" select_type="3" />
      <talk_question mid="5"><![CDATA[<html>$President Vernicka$<BR>I don't know if you're helping me or if you're babysitting for a family.<BR><BR><FONT color=#7e12d2>*You cannot proceed in a party.</FONT></html>]]></talk_question>
   </talk_paragraph>
   <talk_paragraph index="n1816_vernicka-1" image="" itemindex="" portrait_left="" portrait_right="Npc_Left_vernicka.dds" center_image="">
      <talk_answer link_index="n1816_vernicka-1-party_check" mid="72" select_type="2" />
      <talk_question mid="6"><![CDATA[<html>$President Vernicka$<BR>I heard about the <FONT color=#a82424>guardian of Lagendia</FONT> from Hiver.<BR>But there's something that has been bothering me.</html>]]></talk_question>
   </talk_paragraph>
   <talk_paragraph index="n1816_vernicka-1-a" image="" itemindex="" portrait_left="" portrait_right="Npc_Left_vernicka.dds" center_image="">
      <talk_answer link_index="n1816_vernicka-1-b" mid="73" select_type="2" />
      <talk_question mid="7"><![CDATA[<html>${user_nick}$<BR><FONT color=#662500>What is it?</FONT></html>]]></talk_question>
   </talk_paragraph>
   <talk_paragraph index="n1816_vernicka-1-b" image="QN_knight_velskud.dds" itemindex="" portrait_left="" portrait_right="Npc_Left_vernicka.dds" center_image="">
      <talk_answer link_index="n1816_vernicka-1-c" mid="74" select_type="2" />
      <talk_question mid="8"><![CDATA[<html>$President Vernicka$<BR>I heard that when the jewels in this guy called <FONT color=#a82424>Velskud</FONT> are stabilised, you can notice it from Rubinart's jewel that you have, isn't it?</html>]]></talk_question>
   </talk_paragraph>
   <talk_paragraph index="n1816_vernicka-1-c" image="" itemindex="" portrait_left="" portrait_right="Npc_Left_vernicka.dds" center_image="">
      <talk_answer link_index="n1816_vernicka-1-d" mid="75" select_type="2" />
      <talk_question mid="9"><![CDATA[<html>$President Vernicka$<BR>Then why is it that you can't find where Rubinart is with that jewel? Since it's originally from Rubinart, doesn't it know where the other half is?</html>]]></talk_question>
   </talk_paragraph>
   <talk_paragraph index="n1816_vernicka-1-d" image="" itemindex="" portrait_left="" portrait_right="Npc_Left_vernicka.dds" center_image="">
      <talk_answer link_index="n1816_vernicka-1-e" mid="76" select_type="2" />
      <talk_question mid="10"><![CDATA[<html>${user_nick}$<BR><FONT color=#662500>Well, that's because… Rubinart is a </FONT><FONT color=#a82424>Chaos Dragon</FONT><FONT color=#662500> which had been contaminated by Beyond Dragon in the past. So the poison in Mistland makes it hard for the jewel to find each other.</FONT></html>]]></talk_question>
   </talk_paragraph>
   <talk_paragraph index="n1816_vernicka-1-e" image="" itemindex="" portrait_left="" portrait_right="Npc_Left_vernicka.dds" center_image="">
      <talk_answer link_index="n1816_vernicka-1-f" mid="77" select_type="2" />
      <talk_question mid="11"><![CDATA[<html>$President Vernicka$<BR>Then maybe the half of the jewel that you have can't detect the changes in Velskud because of Mistland's poison too.</html>]]></talk_question>
   </talk_paragraph>
   <talk_paragraph index="n1816_vernicka-1-f" image="" itemindex="" portrait_left="" portrait_right="Npc_Left_vernicka.dds" center_image="">
      <talk_answer link_index="n1816_vernicka-1-g" mid="78" select_type="2" />
      <talk_question mid="12"><![CDATA[<html>${user_nick}$<BR><FONT color=#662500>…I never thought about that… But that could be possible.</FONT></html>]]></talk_question>
   </talk_paragraph>
   <talk_paragraph index="n1816_vernicka-1-g" image="" itemindex="" portrait_left="" portrait_right="Npc_Left_vernicka.dds" center_image="">
      <talk_answer link_index="n1816_vernicka-1-h" mid="79" select_type="2" />
      <talk_question mid="13"><![CDATA[<html>$President Vernicka${sound:npc_Vernicka_9718_qu_01.ogg}<BR><FONT color=#7e12d2>(Vernicka shrugs)</FONT><BR>Well, I myself is amazed at how strong Rubinart's barrier is, but we don't know how much longer it can hold up.</html>]]></talk_question>
   </talk_paragraph>
   <talk_paragraph index="n1816_vernicka-1-h" image="" itemindex="" portrait_left="" portrait_right="Npc_Left_vernicka.dds" center_image="">
      <talk_answer link_index="n1816_vernicka-1-i" mid="80" select_type="2" />
      <talk_question mid="14"><![CDATA[<html>$President Vernicka$<BR>I believe Lagendia's dragons evolved in their own ways but the Childs are evolved beings too and yet they can't even handle a barrier created by only half a jewel. Don't you find it strange? It must have hurt Vestinel's pride. Do you think she'll stand by and watch what's happening?</html>]]></talk_question>
   </talk_paragraph>
   <talk_paragraph index="n1816_vernicka-1-i" image="" itemindex="" portrait_left="" portrait_right="Npc_Left_vernicka.dds" center_image="">
      <talk_answer link_index="n1816_vernicka-1-j" mid="81" select_type="2" />
      <talk_question mid="15"><![CDATA[<html>$President Vernicka$<BR>Some say <FONT color=#a82424>another force other than Rubinart</FONT> seems to be involved. But the important thing is that no one knows where that power is coming from so it's not a confirmed fact.</html>]]></talk_question>
   </talk_paragraph>
   <talk_paragraph index="n1816_vernicka-1-j" image="" itemindex="" portrait_left="" portrait_right="Npc_Left_vernicka.dds" center_image="">
      <talk_answer link_index="n1816_vernicka-1-k" mid="82" select_type="2" />
      <talk_question mid="16"><![CDATA[<html>${user_nick}$<BR><FONT color=#662500>Is there any threat of Goddess </FONT><FONT color=#a82424>Vestinel</FONT><FONT color=#662500> breaking Rubinart's force field barrier on her own?</FONT></html>]]></talk_question>
   </talk_paragraph>
   <talk_paragraph index="n1816_vernicka-1-k" image="" itemindex="" portrait_left="" portrait_right="Npc_Left_vernicka.dds" center_image="">
      <talk_answer link_index="n1816_vernicka-1-l" mid="83" select_type="2" />
      <talk_question mid="17"><![CDATA[<html>$President Vernicka$<BR><FONT color=#a82424>Goddess Vestinel</FONT> is hiding in Mistland after creating trouble in the world of gods. She won't leave the <FONT color=#a82424>Oracle</FONT>'s body unless it's something really serious. That would limit her power but at the same time keep her safe from being spotted by the other gods.</html>]]></talk_question>
   </talk_paragraph>
   <talk_paragraph index="n1816_vernicka-1-l" image="" itemindex="" portrait_left="" portrait_right="Npc_Left_vernicka.dds" center_image="">
      <talk_answer link_index="n1816_vernicka-1-m" mid="84" select_type="2" />
      <talk_question mid="18"><![CDATA[<html>$President Vernicka$<BR>Besides, from what I heard from the Order, Rubinart's barrier is in fact <FONT color=#a82424>on the Mistland's side of the Monolith</FONT>. Gods can't fully wield their power in a world they've created with their own hands. Rubinart's barrier is what's keeping Goddess Vestinel from leaving through the Monolith.</html>]]></talk_question>
   </talk_paragraph>
   <talk_paragraph index="n1816_vernicka-1-m" image="" itemindex="" portrait_left="" portrait_right="Npc_Left_vernicka.dds" center_image="">
      <talk_answer link_index="n1816_vernicka-1-n" mid="85" select_type="2" />
      <talk_question mid="19"><![CDATA[<html>$President Vernicka$<BR>Of course she may be able to reach Lagendia through a Dimensional Gap, but her real form is too huge that unless she goes through the Monolith's door, she may destroy the entire Mistland.</html>]]></talk_question>
   </talk_paragraph>
   <talk_paragraph index="n1816_vernicka-1-n" image="" itemindex="" portrait_left="" portrait_right="Npc_Left_vernicka.dds" center_image="">
      <talk_answer link_index="n1816_vernicka-1-o" mid="86" select_type="2" />
      <talk_question mid="20"><![CDATA[<html>$President Vernicka$<BR>So it seems like she doesn’t want to take any risks and break Rubinart's barrier. As I've said before, the problem is that Goddess Vestinel may interfere in ways we can't imagine.</html>]]></talk_question>
   </talk_paragraph>
   <talk_paragraph index="n1816_vernicka-1-o" image="QN_knight_velskud.dds" itemindex="" portrait_left="" portrait_right="Npc_Left_vernicka.dds" center_image="">
      <talk_answer link_index="n1816_vernicka-1-p" mid="87" select_type="2" />
      <talk_question mid="21"><![CDATA[<html>$President Vernicka$<BR>Whatever it is, I don't mean to push you too much. But if you want to see if the jewel you have is really working well, why don't you go and meet <FONT color=#a82424>Velskud</FONT> and check on the situation?</html>]]></talk_question>
   </talk_paragraph>
   <talk_paragraph index="n1816_vernicka-1-p" image="" itemindex="" portrait_left="" portrait_right="Npc_Left_vernicka.dds" center_image="">
      <talk_answer link_index="n1816_vernicka-2" mid="89" select_type="2" />
      <talk_question mid="22"><![CDATA[<html>${user_nick}$<BR><FONT color=#662500>I guess that would be better. I'll go to places where Velskud is most likely to be and find out if the jewel is working.</FONT></html>]]></talk_question>
   </talk_paragraph>
   <talk_paragraph index="n1816_vernicka-1-q" image="" itemindex="" portrait_left="" portrait_right="Npc_Left_vernicka.dds" center_image="">
      <talk_answer link_index="n1816_vernicka-1-" mid="132" select_type="5" />
      <talk_question mid="131"><![CDATA[<html>$President Vernicka$<BR>I'm sorry but please go alone.<BR><BR><FONT color=#7e12d2>*You cannot proceed in a party.</FONT></html>]]></talk_question>
   </talk_paragraph>
   <talk_paragraph index="n1816_vernicka-2" image="QW_105.dds " itemindex="" portrait_left="" portrait_right="Npc_Left_vernicka.dds" center_image="">
      <talk_answer link_index="n1816_vernicka-2-" mid="90" select_type="5" />
      <talk_question mid="23"><![CDATA[<html>${user_nick}$<BR><FONT color=#662500>(I met Velskud at </FONT><FONT color=#a82424>Wasteland Battlefield</FONT><FONT color=#662500> last time… I should start investigating from there.)</FONT></html>]]></talk_question>
   </talk_paragraph>
   <talk_paragraph index="n1807_desert_velskud-2" image="" itemindex="" portrait_left="" portrait_right="Npc_Right_Velskud_Human.dds" center_image="">
      <talk_answer link_index="n1807_desert_velskud-2-a" mid="91" select_type="2" />
      <talk_question mid="24"><![CDATA[<html>$Velskud$<BR>……Just what took you so long?</html>]]></talk_question>
   </talk_paragraph>
   <talk_paragraph index="n1807_desert_velskud-2-a" image="" itemindex="" portrait_left="" portrait_right="Npc_Right_Velskud_Human.dds" center_image="">
      <talk_answer link_index="n1807_desert_velskud-2-b" mid="92" select_type="2" />
      <talk_question mid="25"><![CDATA[<html>${user_nick}$<BR><FONT color=#662500>Huh…? Could it be… Are your jewels stabilised?!</FONT></html>]]></talk_question>
   </talk_paragraph>
   <talk_paragraph index="n1807_desert_velskud-2-b" image="" itemindex="" portrait_left="" portrait_right="Npc_Right_Velskud_Human.dds" center_image="">
      <talk_answer link_index="n1807_desert_velskud-2-c" mid="93" select_type="2" />
      <talk_question mid="26"><![CDATA[<html>$Velskud$<BR>What? Wasn't Rubinart's jewel functioning at all? Hmph. It must have become a junk after being cut into half.</html>]]></talk_question>
   </talk_paragraph>
   <talk_paragraph index="n1807_desert_velskud-2-c" image="" itemindex="" portrait_left="" portrait_right="Npc_Right_Velskud_Human.dds" center_image="">
      <talk_answer link_index="n1807_desert_velskud-2-d" mid="94" select_type="2" />
      <talk_question mid="27"><![CDATA[<html>${user_nick}$<BR><FONT color=#662500>(Wow… I don't think Vernicka knew about this before sending me but he really seems to have a sixth sense...)</FONT></html>]]></talk_question>
   </talk_paragraph>
   <talk_paragraph index="n1807_desert_velskud-2-d" image="" itemindex="" portrait_left="" portrait_right="Npc_Right_Velskud_Human.dds" center_image="">
      <talk_answer link_index="n1807_desert_velskud-2-e" mid="95" select_type="2" />
      <talk_question mid="28"><![CDATA[<html>${user_nick}$<BR><FONT color=#662500>By the way… Have you been waiting here for me all this while?</FONT></html>]]></talk_question>
   </talk_paragraph>
   <talk_paragraph index="n1807_desert_velskud-2-e" image="" itemindex="" portrait_left="" portrait_right="Npc_Right_Velskud_Human.dds" center_image="">
      <talk_answer link_index="n1807_desert_velskud-2-f" mid="96" select_type="2" />
      <talk_question mid="29"><![CDATA[<html>$Velskud${sound:npc_Velskud_9718_qu_01.ogg}<BR>Shut up, idiot. I need to move more quickly because of the delay you've made.</html>]]></talk_question>
   </talk_paragraph>
   <talk_paragraph index="n1807_desert_velskud-2-f" image="" itemindex="" portrait_left="" portrait_right="Npc_Right_Velskud_Human.dds" center_image="">
      <talk_answer link_index="n1807_desert_velskud-2-g" mid="97" select_type="2" />
      <talk_question mid="30"><![CDATA[<html>$Velskud$<BR>Though the jewels are stabilised, there seems to be something wrong with the Monolith's door and it's impossible to close it again. It's probably because of the broken seal stone or Argenta's death... Or maybe there has been a change in Goddess <FONT color=#a82424>Altea</FONT>'s side that we don't know about...</html>]]></talk_question>
   </talk_paragraph>
   <talk_paragraph index="n1807_desert_velskud-2-g" image="" itemindex="" portrait_left="" portrait_right="Npc_Right_Velskud_Human.dds" center_image="">
      <talk_answer link_index="n1807_desert_velskud-2-h" mid="99" select_type="2" />
      <talk_question mid="31"><![CDATA[<html><FONT color=#2b2723>${user_nick}$</FONT><FONT color=#662500><BR>Rubinart also mentioned that it would be hard to close the Monolith again due to certain problems. But if you can't close the door, then how are you going to use the guardian's power?</FONT></html>]]></talk_question>
   </talk_paragraph>
   <talk_paragraph index="n1807_desert_velskud-2-h" image="QN_Npc_Argenta.dds" itemindex="" portrait_left="" portrait_right="Npc_Right_Velskud_Human.dds" center_image="">
      <talk_answer link_index="n1807_desert_velskud-2-i" mid="100" select_type="2" />
      <talk_question mid="32"><![CDATA[<html>$Velskud${sound:npc_Velskud_9718_qu_02.ogg}<BR>Actually, I think <FONT color=#a82424>Argenta</FONT> has been protecting Lagendia with a <FONT color=#a82424>giant force field</FONT>. If I reinstate Argenta's barrier, it would have the same effect as closing the Monolith's door... that's what the sorceresses say.</html>]]></talk_question>
   </talk_paragraph>
   <talk_paragraph index="n1807_desert_velskud-2-i" image="" itemindex="" portrait_left="" portrait_right="Npc_Right_Velskud_Human.dds" center_image="">
      <talk_answer link_index="n1807_desert_velskud-2-j" mid="101" select_type="2" />
      <talk_question mid="33"><![CDATA[<html>$Velskud$<BR>Of course, even with the barrier, it's different from closing the door so it wouldn't stop things other than a physical attack from Mistland, like cracks in the dimensions and distortion in time and space. </html>]]></talk_question>
   </talk_paragraph>
   <talk_paragraph index="n1807_desert_velskud-2-j" image="" itemindex="" portrait_left="" portrait_right="Npc_Right_Velskud_Human.dds" center_image="">
      <talk_answer link_index="n1807_desert_velskud-2-k" mid="102" select_type="2" />
      <talk_question mid="34"><![CDATA[<html><FONT color=#2b2723>${user_nick}$</FONT><FONT color=#662500><BR>But for now, we don’t know when Rubinart's barrier may break, so putting up Argenta's barrier again would be the best chance we have in saving Lagendia.</FONT></html>]]></talk_question>
   </talk_paragraph>
   <talk_paragraph index="n1807_desert_velskud-2-k" image="" itemindex="" portrait_left="" portrait_right="Npc_Right_Velskud_Human.dds" center_image="">
      <talk_answer link_index="n1807_desert_velskud-3" mid="103" select_type="2" />
      <talk_question mid="35"><![CDATA[<html>$Velskud$<BR>Follow me if you've understood what I said.<BR><FONT color=#7e12d2>(Velskud walks over to what seems to be a Dimensional Gap.)</FONT></html>]]></talk_question>
   </talk_paragraph>
   <talk_paragraph index="n1807_desert_velskud-3" image="" itemindex="" portrait_left="" portrait_right="Npc_Right_Velskud_Human.dds" center_image="">
      <talk_answer link_index="n1807_desert_velskud-3-party_check" mid="134" select_type="2" />
      <talk_question mid="36"><![CDATA[<html>$Velskud$<BR>…………….</html>]]></talk_question>
   </talk_paragraph>
   <talk_paragraph index="n1807_desert_velskud-3-a" image="" itemindex="" portrait_left="" portrait_right="" center_image="">
      <talk_answer link_index="n1807_desert_velskud-3-b" mid="136" select_type="5" />
      <talk_question mid="135"><![CDATA[<html>$Velskud$<BR>What? Don't tell me you can't do anything without your friends.<BR>
What a useless trash.<BR>
<BR>
<BR>
<FONT color=#7e12d2>*You cannot proceed in a party.</FONT></html>]]></talk_question>
   </talk_paragraph>
